cial and artistic discussions through their work and became a transformative part of American culture over time. Anastasia Aukeman presents new and little-known archival material in this authorized account of these artists and their circle, a colorful cultural milieu that intersected with the broader Beat scene.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 4aArt & Politics. 4aArt. 7aART / Art & Politics.2bisacsh1 aAukeman, Anastasia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106675470 cprintz978052028946840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052035619140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520356191423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520356191/original  a978-3-11-066754-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles